that didn't have public
lands or parks or a tradition

44:50.466 --> 44:52.533 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
of that.

44:52.533 --> 44:56.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so we are reaching the
kids and they're bringing
their parents to the parks.

44:58.866 --> 45:02.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: Jon Jarvis,
the director of the National
Park Service, says America's

45:02.966 --> 45:06.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
